image.caption: Black clouds hang over the Bangabandhu national stadium in Dhaka
image.longCaption: Black clouds hang over Banghabandhu nation stadium in Dhaka as the pitch is covered with plastic 20 April 2003. South African and India are to play the final match of the TVS tri-nation cricket tournament, but heavy rain stopped the match before it could start

milestones.description: This is the highest match aggregate (605) involving teams India & Bangladesh in ODIs

stories.title: 'We were very upset after yesterday' - Sehwag
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v India, 3rd ODI, Dhaka
stories.summary: Virender Sehwag, the Man of the Match in the deciding game of the series, admitted that the Indian team were very upset with their shock loss in the second game, and wanted to make certain there was no repeat of the fiasco

stories.title: A small redemption
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v India, 2nd ODI, Dhaka
stories.summary: It took a humiliating defeat and the spectre of unspeakable ignominy to rouse the Indian batsmen to come up with a performance befitting their stature
stories.byline: The Wisden Verdict by Sambit Bal

stories.title: India seal comprehensive win
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v India, 3rd ODI, Dhaka
stories.summary: India crushed Bangladesh by a whopping margin of 91 runs and romped home to a series victory
stories.byline: The Bulletin by Anand Vasu in Dhaka
